description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to make a difference for people with ADHD?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our adult Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD) clinic, a specialist service offering assessments for adults with possible ADHD and previously diagnosed ADHD, is offering an opportunity to support their work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting role is available for a highly organised, motivated and enthusiastic person. The Band 3 Administrator position is located at Fulbourn Hospital within the Adult and Specialist Administration Hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The working pattern is Monday to Thursday 10-2, Friday 10-12.45.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be well organised and able to prioritise work. You will be proactive in solving problems and queries which you will see through to completion. The post holder will need to be calm and patient with an excellent telephone manner and skills to deal with sometimes complex and difficult issues. You will have good IT skills and experience in a busy office environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have a strong team work ethic, sense of accountability, accompanied by an ability to work under considerable pressure at times. This post is open to professionals with the right attributes to enhance a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide the necessary support to ensure your development in your role. We are keen to support and develop our staff through a clear career pathway and encourage promotional opportunities within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Daniel Ingram - Senior Administrator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;daniel.ingram@cpft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
